Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_module_model(25.10)                            check_module_model(25.10)

Name
       check_module_model  -  Checks  and validates an ILM model to see if the
       current reduction ratio will cause any missing constraints at the hinst
       terminal or any slack difference

Syntax
       check_module_model

       [-help]

       -cell <cell_name>

       [-out_file <file_name>]

       -ref_tag <tag_name>

       [-slack_threshold <threshold>] [-type {flexIlm ilm pnr}]

       Checks and validates an ILM model to see if the current reduction ratio
       will cause any missing constraints at the hinst terminal or  any  slack
       difference.  The  check_module_model command compares/checks the target
       timing result with the reference timing result and generates a  summary
       and detailed report.

       Note:  If  a specified cell has more than one instantiated modules, all
       hinst terminals are checked and reported.

       Usage Model:

              * Generate a reference ILM model with the   createInterfaceLogic
                -keepAll  option  and  a  target ILM model with user-specified
                settings.

              * Restore  the  top-level  design  and  set/commit  target   ILM
                model(s).

              * Time the design.

              * Call check_module_model

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each check_module_model  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man check_module_model

       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the ILM cell name that will be validated.

              Data_type: string, required

       -out_file <file_name>
              Specifies the output report file.

              Default: ./check_module_model.rpt

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ref_tag <tag_name>
              Specifies the reference tag name of the reference ILM model.

              Data_type: string, required

       -slack_threshold <threshold>
              Specified  the  slack threshold for reporting the number of mis-
              matched slacks over the threshold.

              Default: 0.0005

              Data_type: string, optional

       -type {flexIlm ilm pnr}
              Specifies the type of module model. The model type can be  flex-
              Ilm, ilm, or pnr.

              Default: ilm

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The  following command check the tdsp_core cell and writes the
                detailed report in the tdsp_check_module_model.rpt file:

                check_module_model -cell tdsp_core -ref_tag  ref_preCts  -type
                ilm  -out_file tdsp_check_module_model.rpt

